1
00:00:03,303 --> 00:00:07,374
I'm sorry to say
but Otowado's merger has been decided.

2
00:00:07,407 --> 00:00:10,043
And Miyavi will most likely
be discontinued.

3
00:00:10,878 --> 00:00:13,714
But we're not over yet.

4
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:21,488
Otowado, the publishing firm
that I, Nami Suzuki, work at,

5
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:24,224
is on the verge of being taken over.

6
00:00:26,093 --> 00:00:26,894
Amidst all this,

7
00:00:27,194 --> 00:00:32,332
Ms. Horai laid her eyes on Isobe,
a company that created lotion from silk.

8
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:38,872
Miyavi succeeded in securing
a collaborative production with Coach.

9
00:00:39,172 --> 00:00:42,976
Sericin is the perfect
natural moisturizing agent.

10
00:00:43,010 --> 00:00:47,247
I'd like to create
a green organic theme for Coach.

11
00:00:47,748 --> 00:00:50,517
Our last chance to pull through...

12
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:55,255
Whether Miyavi can continue or not
all depends on this project.

13
00:00:56,323 --> 00:01:01,094
That night was also the night
I missed the last train.

14
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:04,164
And Junnosuke came all the way
to pick me up.

15
00:01:05,365 --> 00:01:09,870
We've gotten so much closer
since then.

16
00:01:11,271 --> 00:01:14,341
This morning, too.

17
00:01:23,383 --> 00:01:25,652
I made omelets over rice
for breakfast.

18
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:28,555
Breakfast omelets.

19
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:30,357
Looks yummy.

20
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:32,426
Nami.

21
00:01:35,896 --> 00:01:36,763
Say thank you.

22
00:01:42,536 --> 00:01:43,603
All right!

23
00:01:44,905 --> 00:01:48,008
How cute is this little puppy!

24
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:53,180
It's White Jun!

25
00:02:00,554 --> 00:02:01,355
Suzuki?

26
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:04,925
Don't cry yet.

27
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:08,862
Sorry.

28
00:02:08,895 --> 00:02:11,632
The collaboration project
is shaping up.

29
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,067
It may be a vain struggle.

30
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:17,504
That new brand by Mr. Shintani.

31
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:20,774
They're putting an exclusive ad
in the next Zeal.

32
00:02:23,176 --> 00:02:24,878
Your vain struggle.

33
00:02:25,679 --> 00:02:27,514
Let me in on it too.

34
00:02:30,951 --> 00:02:31,718
Kanazawa City
Ishikawa

35
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:32,652
I'm home.

36
00:02:32,686 --> 00:02:33,887
You're home.

37
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,188
I want some too.

38
00:02:37,391 --> 00:02:38,692
Junnosuke!

39
00:02:38,725 --> 00:02:41,528
You should've called
if you were coming home.

40
00:02:41,561 --> 00:02:43,497
Why? It's my home too.

41
00:02:44,364 --> 00:02:47,234
I actually came to tell you
I'm coming home.

42
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:51,805
Once I finish all the gigs I have now,
I'll come back home.

43
00:02:52,472 --> 00:02:54,274
I'll run the Horai Group.

44
00:02:55,742 --> 00:02:59,112
You guys let me do what I wanted
all this time.

45
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:01,381
I guess it's about time.

46
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,019
You've finally come around.

47
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:08,789
I must call your father.

48
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:14,428
About that girlfriend
you said you had.

49
00:03:14,461 --> 00:03:15,762
Bring her over.

50
00:03:15,796 --> 00:03:18,298
She'll be coming
to Kanazawa someday, right?

51
00:03:18,732 --> 00:03:20,267
The earlier the better.

52
00:03:21,101 --> 00:03:24,071
Honey, what time will you
come home tonight?

53
00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:27,007
I have some wonderful news!

54
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:29,276
It's about Junnosuke.

55
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,084
Okay.

56
00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:43,290
Ms. Kazumi, here's the material
you wanted. Here.

57
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:45,125
Suzuki.

58
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:47,794
Do you want to write
Mr. Isobe's introduction?

59
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,197
I can?

60
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,332
Suzuki is debuting!

61
00:03:52,365 --> 00:03:55,035
It's just 200 letters but here you go.

62
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,404
Okay, a 200-letter introduction.

63
00:03:58,038 --> 00:03:59,206
I'll do my best!

64
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,052
I'm home.

65
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:22,963
Sorry for waking you.
You don't have to get up.

66
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:24,931
It's okay.

67
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:27,267
You worked late today.

68
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:33,440
Everyone is busy preparing
for the lotion I told you about.

69
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:38,145
And we still have to work on
the next issue like always.

70
00:04:38,345 --> 00:04:39,579
It's so hectic.

71
00:04:43,517 --> 00:04:45,785
I get to write in it.

72
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:47,888
You're writing in Miyavi?

73
00:04:49,055 --> 00:04:52,926
It's just a simple introduction
of Mr. Isobe.

74
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:55,962
Here.

75
00:04:56,496 --> 00:04:57,931
Like these.

76
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:01,601
See?

77
00:05:02,035 --> 00:05:04,838
A short 200-letter introduction
by the picture.

78
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:07,374
But I can't get it shorter than 1000.

79
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,844
That's incredible. Good for you.

80
00:05:14,014 --> 00:05:15,115
Kanazawa?

81
00:05:15,849 --> 00:05:16,883
I went home today.

82
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:18,852
Want some? I'll make tea.

83
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:20,787
It's okay, I got it.

84
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:28,028
It's pretty weird
if you think about it.

85
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:32,465
You were born in Kanazawa,
and I was born in Kumamoto.

86
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:36,770
And here we are, together now.
Feels strange.

87
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:40,974
Kumamoto Prefecture

88
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:45,412
I want to go to Kanazawa someday too.

89
00:05:46,546 --> 00:05:49,382
She'll be coming
to Kanazawa someday, right?

90
00:05:51,418 --> 00:05:54,921
Not just Kanazawa.
But I want to go somewhere with you.

91
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:01,661
Then let's go on a date
once the next Miyavi is out.

92
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:03,430
Yeah!

93
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:33,760
Pick up two Loewe bags
from Omotesando.

94
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:38,064
And a bouquet for Mr. Kono
of Emilio Pucci. And...

95
00:06:39,499 --> 00:06:40,433
May I have a minute?

96
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,468
Come in.

97
00:06:43,536 --> 00:06:45,272
Ms. Suzuki.

98
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:48,642
I'm sorry,
but can we have some privacy?

99
00:06:50,143 --> 00:06:51,278
Ah, yes.

100
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:57,017
You see.

101
00:06:58,451 --> 00:06:59,586
We have a problem.

102
00:07:03,523 --> 00:07:06,326
Charismatic editor-in-chief
and workplace harassment?

103
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,162
Is that Ms. Horai and Ms. Suzuki?

104
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:12,565
This was sent to our department
this morning.

105
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,968
I think that's what
they're talking about.

106
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:16,336
What is it?

107
00:07:16,369 --> 00:07:19,105
This is going out
in next week's tabloid.

108
00:07:21,241 --> 00:07:22,042
Is that me?

109
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:24,844
- Workplace harassment?
- Shh!

110
00:07:25,679 --> 00:07:27,580
They're totally right.

111
00:07:27,914 --> 00:07:30,216
I wanted everyone to know
how tough I had it.

112
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,518
So it was you?

113
00:07:31,985 --> 00:07:33,253
You spilled it, huh?

114
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:36,089
No way, of course not.

115
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:41,428
It says this assistant was
even left behind in the mountains.

116
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,762
Totally exaggerated.

117
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:45,965
I wouldn't put it past her,
but she hasn't yet.

118
00:07:45,999 --> 00:07:48,935
Who talked? It's not even correct.

119
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:50,070
Forget that for now.

120
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:53,306
How will Coach and Mr. Isobe feel?

121
00:07:54,074 --> 00:07:56,376
Mr. Isobe is risking a lot for us.

122
00:07:59,612 --> 00:08:01,815
Suzuki, get me a taxi.

123
00:08:03,116 --> 00:08:03,917
Yes.

124
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:27,774
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

125
00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:32,512
We are so sorry for what has happened.

126
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,447
Forgive us.

127
00:08:34,981 --> 00:08:37,817
I'm not in the publishing business.

128
00:08:38,118 --> 00:08:41,521
So I wouldn't be able to tell
if this were true or not.

129
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:44,824
But as you see,
we're a small business.

130
00:08:48,461 --> 00:08:52,232
I had some advice from a friend
concerning Otowado's finances.

131
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:57,637
Some employers are worried
about this collaboration project.

132
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,908
I don't know if continuing it
is the right decision.

133
00:09:02,308 --> 00:09:05,445
I can't make the decision
on my own anymore.

134
00:09:08,848 --> 00:09:11,551
I understand
I'm not in the position to say.

135
00:09:12,152 --> 00:09:14,354
But won't you believe in her?

136
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:24,330
The project is stopped for now?

137
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:25,899
I understand.

138
00:09:28,034 --> 00:09:29,102
Mr. Handa.

139
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:35,208
We can't work on it anymore
until Isobe consents.

140
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,544
But we'll run out of time.

141
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:40,513
Can't we just work on it
for when they do consent?

142
00:09:40,547 --> 00:09:45,218
No. If it's not commercialized,
the article would go to waste.

143
00:09:46,386 --> 00:09:48,988
We can't risk that now,
with finances as they are.

144
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,626
What's with this anyways?

145
00:09:54,861 --> 00:09:57,430
Are you sure it wasn't one of us?

146
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,266
Maybe there's a rat.

147
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,868
Don't be stupid.

148
00:10:01,901 --> 00:10:05,104
But there's stuff in there
only we would know.

149
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,040
How about it?

150
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,677
Stop it, now!

151
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:16,182
It must've been somebody
that was jealous of Miyavi's success.

152
00:10:16,483 --> 00:10:19,853
Now is not the time to point fingers.

153
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,922
Once Otowado is taken over and
Miyavi discontinued,

154
00:10:22,956 --> 00:10:24,824
this team will be broken up.

155
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:31,397
That's what they want, for us
to start distrusting one another.

156
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:37,971
You're right, Mr. Handa.

157
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:40,840
Sorry for what I said.

158
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:43,543
Even if the project falls through,

159
00:10:43,576 --> 00:10:45,845
the next Miyavi
will still be published.

160
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:47,213
Let's do what we can.

161
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:53,620
Sorry.

162
00:10:54,087 --> 00:10:56,990
But thanks for everything
all this time.

163
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:02,462
What did Nami say
about you quitting photography?

164
00:11:04,531 --> 00:11:06,633
- I haven't told her yet.
- But!

165
00:11:06,933 --> 00:11:09,536
Forget about me, you have to tell her.

166
00:11:12,705 --> 00:11:15,575
She's working so hard right now.

167
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:17,810
If I say I'm going home now,

168
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:20,613
it'd be like making her choose
between me and work.

169
00:11:21,481 --> 00:11:22,448
You know?

170
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:25,318
If you don't tell her,
she can't even choose.

171
00:11:26,252 --> 00:11:28,621
It's up to her to decide, not you.

172
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:32,825
I don't know.

173
00:11:36,829 --> 00:11:37,997
What's that?

174
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:40,500
I found this in her room.

175
00:11:42,969 --> 00:11:45,872
"Ten things I want to do
when I get a boyfriend"?

176
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:51,244
We've just started to date,
and look how happy she is.

177
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:09,228
Mr. Nakazawa.

178
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:15,401
Thank you for finding my bracelet.

179
00:12:16,035 --> 00:12:17,503
That was you, wasn't it?

180
00:12:22,675 --> 00:12:24,310
I just happened to see it.

181
00:12:28,047 --> 00:12:29,182
And...

182
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,653
About the answer
I'd kept you waiting for.

183
00:12:39,692 --> 00:12:42,996
I'm really grateful
for how you feel about me.

184
00:12:44,297 --> 00:12:46,566
But, um...

185
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:50,269
To me, you're a senpai
that I really respect.

186
00:12:50,837 --> 00:12:53,106
- So...
- Suzuki.

187
00:12:58,144 --> 00:12:59,612
I was kidding.

188
00:13:02,548 --> 00:13:03,716
It was just a joke.

189
00:13:04,484 --> 00:13:08,421
Did you really think
I'd fall in love with you?

190
00:13:16,896 --> 00:13:19,932
Yeah, sorry. Never mind.

191
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:24,203
But really, don't worry about it.

192
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:44,557
Mr. Nakazawa.

193
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:46,526
Yeah, what's up?

194
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:48,494
A movie.

195
00:13:50,797 --> 00:13:53,199
Can you give me a recommendation?

196
00:13:55,435 --> 00:13:56,703
Why now?

197
00:13:57,970 --> 00:14:03,576
A story about how after a heartbreak,
true love was actually so close by.

198
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:06,846
That's so corny.

199
00:14:08,748 --> 00:14:09,716
I know.

200
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:11,951
But sure, I'll think about it.

201
00:14:31,104 --> 00:14:31,904
Nami.

202
00:14:35,141 --> 00:14:36,175
Junnosuke.

203
00:14:36,743 --> 00:14:38,010
Did you just get off work?

204
00:14:39,078 --> 00:14:40,313
What's with the low voice?

205
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:44,684
- Have a seat.
- Huh?

206
00:14:46,152 --> 00:14:47,153
Where's your bike?

207
00:14:48,488 --> 00:14:50,556
I thought this would be fun for once.

208
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:53,893
Want to go to a photo booth?

209
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,963
What's wrong? You're acting weird.

210
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:58,197
Am I?

211
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:02,535
Yeah, you're talking
in a weird deep voice.

212
00:15:03,035 --> 00:15:05,471
Are you really Junnosuke?

213
00:15:06,372 --> 00:15:10,109
I just felt like it.

214
00:15:10,143 --> 00:15:12,245
And just happened to ride my bicycle.

215
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,747
Okay, whatever.

216
00:15:15,014 --> 00:15:16,682
Come on, get on.

217
00:15:17,884 --> 00:15:21,320
But double riding in the streets
is against the law.

218
00:15:22,054 --> 00:15:22,789
It is?

219
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:24,657
But you wrote...

220
00:15:26,793 --> 00:15:27,994
Nothing.

221
00:15:30,563 --> 00:15:33,633
I'm going home to my place,
so let's talk on the phone.

222
00:15:35,735 --> 00:15:36,736
Later.

223
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:43,943
Can't we talk now?

224
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:47,680
Yes, hello?

225
00:15:48,214 --> 00:15:49,182
What is it?

226
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:52,118
Nami... I mean.

227
00:15:52,852 --> 00:15:54,453
I wanted to hear your voice.

228
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,023
I really don't get it.

229
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:58,224
Is it a prank?

230
00:15:58,925 --> 00:16:01,260
Of course not, Nami.

231
00:16:02,028 --> 00:16:06,265
It's weird with you talking like that.

232
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:09,202
- Can you just talk like normal?
- Really?

233
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:12,338
Okay, Nami.

234
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:21,814
Can I hang up now?

235
00:16:21,848 --> 00:16:24,283
- Goodnight.
- No wait!

236
00:16:26,252 --> 00:16:27,553
Do you have anything to say?

237
00:16:27,587 --> 00:16:29,488
No, not really.

238
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:32,325
Come on, anything. Are you sleepy yet?

239
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:33,559
Not really.

240
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:35,194
Darn.

241
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,363
What's going on?

242
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:41,400
So, how are things, Nami?

243
00:16:42,268 --> 00:16:46,038
Things are actually kind of rough now.

244
00:16:47,273 --> 00:16:49,542
Some bizarre story
came out about Ms. Horai.

245
00:16:49,575 --> 00:16:52,445
And the project we were working on
has stopped.

246
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:54,947
And the merger too.

247
00:16:54,981 --> 00:16:57,183
Will you go to the new company then?

248
00:16:57,516 --> 00:17:00,219
I really like the editing team.

249
00:17:00,553 --> 00:17:02,188
I wish nothing had to change.

250
00:17:04,357 --> 00:17:05,424
Yeah.

251
00:17:06,392 --> 00:17:07,326
I get what you mean.

252
00:17:09,428 --> 00:17:13,833
It's become a special place for you,
hasn't it?

253
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:21,741
Morning.

254
00:17:22,341 --> 00:17:23,542
Mr. Isobe.

255
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:29,348
Ms. Horai and Mr. Ugajin
have already come to me.

256
00:17:30,283 --> 00:17:32,251
I've nothing more to say.

257
00:17:32,285 --> 00:17:34,987
That article is a lie!

258
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:37,490
She would never do such a thing.

259
00:17:38,124 --> 00:17:40,960
She's just like Mother Teresa.

260
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:42,361
Right?

261
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:49,702
It takes time to build trust.

262
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:53,172
What am I to trust now?

263
00:17:53,205 --> 00:17:57,243
Your words
or the story in the article?

264
00:17:58,010 --> 00:17:59,545
What are you doing?

265
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:04,550
Ms. Horai!

266
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:07,987
No, I...

267
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:11,290
Suzuki insisted on speaking
with Mr. Isobe and...

268
00:18:11,324 --> 00:18:12,925
I called her here.

269
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:14,560
You did?

270
00:18:16,562 --> 00:18:19,665
This is none of your business.
You're just an assistant.

271
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,968
But the article was about me too.

272
00:18:28,207 --> 00:18:28,975
Mr. Isobe.

273
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:34,113
Suzuki!

274
00:18:35,715 --> 00:18:40,519
It's true that Ms. Horai's words
may seem like workplace harassment.

275
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:46,425
But her harsh words and
seemingly unjust actions

276
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:51,197
are all for making a better magazine.

277
00:18:55,034 --> 00:18:56,235
Look.

278
00:18:58,838 --> 00:19:00,706
Did he ask for your opinion?

279
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:03,509
Did I ask you?

280
00:19:03,943 --> 00:19:07,313
You may speak
only when I allow you to.

281
00:19:08,414 --> 00:19:09,415
Stay out of this.

282
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:10,549
You shouldn't...

283
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:11,517
I will not.

284
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:21,527
If you can't do as I ask,
you may quit now.

285
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,862
That's harassment...!

286
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,631
I won't quit.

287
00:19:26,265 --> 00:19:29,568
If that were enough to make me quit,
I'd be long gone.

288
00:19:29,802 --> 00:19:30,569
Suzuki!

289
00:19:33,072 --> 00:19:38,444
Ordering me around all the time.
I wanted to quit so badly.

290
00:19:39,145 --> 00:19:41,047
But when I see the finished magazine,

291
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:46,052
I get happy because I know
I helped make it.

292
00:19:47,686 --> 00:19:49,121
So I'm not quitting.

293
00:19:50,423 --> 00:19:54,093
As long as you're here,
I'm your only assistant.

294
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:56,695
Hey!

295
00:19:57,129 --> 00:20:00,633
If only you worked as well as
your self-righteous speech.

296
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:02,535
Self-righteous?

297
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:09,075
Besides, nobody else would be able
to last a week working under you.

298
00:20:09,108 --> 00:20:09,742
Suzuki...

299
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:13,512
If they're as useless as you are,
I don't need one.

300
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:16,649
Useless? You used me for
a bunch of stuff.

301
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,017
Oh did I?

302
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,652
That kendama at the party.

303
00:20:19,685 --> 00:20:21,520
That's because you lied.

304
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:25,057
And you took so long
preparing that gift,

305
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:27,059
- I had to talk...
- Excuse me.

306
00:20:29,361 --> 00:20:32,331
That's enough. I see clearly now.

307
00:20:32,364 --> 00:20:34,200
Oh dear.

308
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:40,339
Well, well.

309
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:44,710
It's worse than
what was in that article.

310
00:20:48,447 --> 00:20:52,518
I'm going to believe in you.

311
00:20:59,058 --> 00:21:00,459
Thank you!

312
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:12,138
To think I'd work with you someday.

313
00:21:12,171 --> 00:21:13,906
Anything for you, Sis.

314
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,342
Miyavi might stay in print.

315
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:18,077
I'm not going to lose either.

316
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,945
I'll never forget you.

317
00:21:19,979 --> 00:21:21,614
I want to be a part of a team.

318
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:24,250
Nami made those feelings become real.

319
00:21:30,723 --> 00:21:32,892
Yes, right away.

320
00:21:34,527 --> 00:21:36,162
Isobe agreed to resume.

321
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:38,898
Let's get back to work.

322
00:21:39,265 --> 00:21:43,068
- All right!
- Yes!

323
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:52,011
Yes, the project will resume now.

324
00:21:52,077 --> 00:21:54,613
You did that on purpose, didn't you?

325
00:21:57,116 --> 00:22:02,555
I wondered how I could make Mr. Isobe
understand the person you really are.

326
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:04,557
I gave it a lot of thought.

327
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:07,726
Lies don't turn into the truth.

328
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:10,663
So I didn't want to lie
about anything.

329
00:22:12,198 --> 00:22:14,934
What would you have done
if I didn't go with it?

330
00:22:17,837 --> 00:22:20,573
I knew that you would.

331
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:24,577
It was a good presentation.

332
00:22:25,477 --> 00:22:26,278
Really?

333
00:22:26,579 --> 00:22:31,050
I don't know how it happened,
but they've become such a good pair.

334
00:22:31,116 --> 00:22:32,284
Good day.

335
00:22:34,486 --> 00:22:37,590
Huh? We don't get to ride with her?

336
00:22:38,057 --> 00:22:40,326
What's going on?

337
00:22:41,927 --> 00:22:43,862
- We're back.
- Hi.

338
00:22:44,029 --> 00:22:46,498
Suzuki, are you done
with the introduction?

339
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:48,701
Yes, will you check it please?

340
00:22:49,068 --> 00:22:52,137
Hello, I'm back.

341
00:22:52,171 --> 00:22:55,241
Mr. Ogasawara,
we were waiting for you.

342
00:22:55,808 --> 00:22:57,710
Proofreading, right? I'm ready.

343
00:22:58,310 --> 00:23:00,246
Look at all this energy.

344
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:04,617
What is it?

345
00:23:04,617 --> 00:23:07,453
- We're in huge trouble.
- What?

346
00:23:07,519 --> 00:23:10,422
The photographer I had in mind
got booked.

347
00:23:10,422 --> 00:23:11,991
For the lotion article?

348
00:23:12,157 --> 00:23:15,160
Another gig came up
while we had put him on hold.

349
00:23:15,728 --> 00:23:18,264
We'll have to find
a different photographer.

350
00:23:18,998 --> 00:23:20,332
Does anybody know of one?

351
00:23:20,366 --> 00:23:22,167
But it's tomorrow.

352
00:23:23,435 --> 00:23:26,372
Suzuki. You know one, don't you?

353
00:23:26,905 --> 00:23:27,906
No, I don't.

354
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:52,765
Nami

355
00:23:56,568 --> 00:23:57,202
Can you bring those plants in
the center a little more to the front?

356
00:23:57,202 --> 00:24:01,407
Otowado basement studio

357
00:24:03,409 --> 00:24:05,144
Good morning.

358
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:06,745
Good morning.

359
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:09,214
Thanks for having us today.

360
00:24:09,415 --> 00:24:11,383
- Hello.
- Hi.

361
00:24:11,417 --> 00:24:13,686
Thanks, Junnosuke.

362
00:24:15,321 --> 00:24:17,589
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

363
00:24:17,656 --> 00:24:21,427
I will be today's cameraman.
My name is Junnosuke Horai.

364
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:22,594
Nice to meet you.

365
00:24:22,661 --> 00:24:24,129
Nice to meet you.

366
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:26,765
To think I'd work with you someday.

367
00:24:27,599 --> 00:24:30,336
Anything for you, Sis.

368
00:24:32,438 --> 00:24:35,140
What did you just say?

369
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,543
- Sis?
- What do you mean?

370
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,978
You guys didn't know?

371
00:24:40,913 --> 00:24:42,181
She's my big sister.

372
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:46,452
Seriously?

373
00:24:47,453 --> 00:24:49,621
Oh yeah, I hadn't told them.

374
00:24:59,264 --> 00:25:00,466
Can I have a full shot?

375
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:09,708
Okay.

376
00:25:12,378 --> 00:25:13,278
Let's check it.

377
00:25:13,912 --> 00:25:14,713
Ms. Horai.

378
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:27,760
Good.

379
00:25:31,096 --> 00:25:32,030
Okay.

380
00:25:32,664 --> 00:25:33,399
Good work.

381
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:37,035
Thank you! Great work.

382
00:25:41,940 --> 00:25:43,108
Mr. Jun...

383
00:25:43,509 --> 00:25:46,779
You were truly the man
up until the last day!

384
00:26:06,365 --> 00:26:07,332
Sis.

385
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:11,136
Nami.

386
00:26:16,809 --> 00:26:18,343
Let me officially introduce you.

387
00:26:18,811 --> 00:26:21,180
This is Nami, my girlfriend.

388
00:26:22,881 --> 00:26:26,452
It's not for pretend.
She's my real girlfriend.

389
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:32,558
- Who would've imagined?
- Why not?

390
00:26:33,358 --> 00:26:36,562
Nami isn't really the best cook.

391
00:26:36,628 --> 00:26:40,432
But she looks up recipes for
omelets over rice and makes it for me.

392
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:43,202
Her candid way of speaking is cute.

393
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:47,673
She's not career-oriented like you.

394
00:26:47,906 --> 00:26:50,742
But I can tell that she loves her job.

395
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:52,845
That's what I like about her.

396
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:58,417
It was pretend back then.

397
00:26:59,318 --> 00:27:01,854
Nami made those feelings become real.

398
00:27:06,325 --> 00:27:07,292
Well.

399
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:10,863
I'm busy, I have to go.

400
00:27:18,937 --> 00:27:20,606
What was that about?

401
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:24,042
I wanted to introduce you
to my family.

402
00:27:42,194 --> 00:27:42,961
Hey.

403
00:27:44,696 --> 00:27:45,797
Good work today.

404
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:49,301
Hey.

405
00:27:54,106 --> 00:27:58,277
Remember how I asked you how love
was about winning and losing?

406
00:28:00,379 --> 00:28:02,147
Maybe it is.

407
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:07,519
I'm not giving her up to you.

408
00:28:08,887 --> 00:28:09,922
I'm not going to lose.

409
00:28:15,027 --> 00:28:16,061
Yeah.

410
00:28:17,029 --> 00:28:18,730
I'm not going to lose either.

411
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:22,301
Later.

412
00:28:29,341 --> 00:28:30,909
- Good morning.
- The latest Slash issue is in.

413
00:28:30,909 --> 00:28:31,977
Workplace harassment
by editor-in-chief

414
00:28:31,977 --> 00:28:34,179
Why do they even do this?

415
00:28:35,414 --> 00:28:38,016
People write them
because people read them.

416
00:28:39,017 --> 00:28:40,185
Sorry.

417
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:43,956
We can't let it get to us.

418
00:28:43,989 --> 00:28:46,091
Come on, back to work!

419
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,126
Excuse me.

420
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:50,796
About these receipts.

421
00:28:50,829 --> 00:28:53,565
Oh yeah, I have some
to reimburse, too.

422
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:58,136
- You're so clumsy.
- Sorry.

423
00:28:59,571 --> 00:29:00,005
Shunbunsha
Yoshio Morishima

424
00:29:00,005 --> 00:29:01,173
Shunbunsha?

425
00:29:01,206 --> 00:29:04,710
I met him when I went out drinking.

426
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:07,913
We hit it off when we found out
we were both in publishing.

427
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,117
Did you tell him about Ms. Horai?

428
00:29:13,085 --> 00:29:14,286
Why?

429
00:29:17,723 --> 00:29:20,325
This magazine is by Shunbunsha.

430
00:29:25,197 --> 00:29:28,133
Mr. Handa...

431
00:29:28,166 --> 00:29:29,067
Me?

432
00:29:30,202 --> 00:29:31,269
It was me?

433
00:29:31,703 --> 00:29:33,138
Sorry, Jun.

434
00:29:34,973 --> 00:29:37,009
I'm the one that should apologize.

435
00:29:37,843 --> 00:29:38,777
About what?

436
00:29:39,077 --> 00:29:41,580
I said I'd go
to the hospital with you.

437
00:29:43,315 --> 00:29:45,117
What, that?

438
00:29:45,484 --> 00:29:47,152
You were really going to come?

439
00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:50,188
You said you might not be able
to play anymore.

440
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:54,126
Yeah, okay.

441
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,229
So you were worried about me?

442
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:01,233
Of course I was.
You're my childhood friend.

443
00:30:03,869 --> 00:30:04,803
Thanks.

444
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:06,772
So?

445
00:30:07,539 --> 00:30:08,507
How was it?

446
00:30:17,082 --> 00:30:19,017
It was just an inflamed tendon.

447
00:30:19,051 --> 00:30:22,688
He told me I was practicing too much
and that I had to rest.

448
00:30:22,721 --> 00:30:23,955
Can you believe it?

449
00:30:25,257 --> 00:30:27,259
So it'll get better?

450
00:30:27,292 --> 00:30:28,927
Yeah, totally.

451
00:30:32,964 --> 00:30:35,000
I'm so relieved.

452
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,968
Thanks for worrying about me.

453
00:30:37,969 --> 00:30:38,837
Bye.

454
00:30:47,946 --> 00:30:50,682
Focal dystonia

455
00:31:00,258 --> 00:31:03,028
And finally, the third issue
of Miyavi was complete.

456
00:31:03,962 --> 00:31:05,030
At the same time,

457
00:31:05,063 --> 00:31:09,568
the skin lotion by Coach, Isobe,
and Miyavi hit the market.

458
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:15,941
But depending on today's board
meeting, Miyavi may be discontinued.

459
00:31:15,974 --> 00:31:18,410
The board meeting is about to start.

460
00:31:18,443 --> 00:31:19,978
I can't sit still.

461
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:22,881
Not that doing anything
will help out the situation.

462
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:26,218
Sales are as usual.

463
00:31:27,652 --> 00:31:31,523
There are hardly any merits
to keep Otowado's magazines in print.

464
00:31:32,457 --> 00:31:37,329
To discontinue every magazine
or to keep them in print.

465
00:31:37,562 --> 00:31:39,498
Let us put it to a vote.

466
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,375
- What?
- Look!

467
00:31:52,277 --> 00:31:53,178
Fuwa?

468
00:31:53,211 --> 00:31:55,147
She put up a post
about our skin lotion.

469
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:58,250
Oh my gosh, look!
Over 1,000 comments!

470
00:31:58,283 --> 00:32:01,286
Look, Ahn Mika posted it too!

471
00:32:01,319 --> 00:32:02,921
Look at all these comments.

472
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:04,422
Thank you, Fuwa and Ahn Mika!

473
00:32:04,456 --> 00:32:08,460
Maybe we can keep Miyavi
from being discontinued.

474
00:32:10,128 --> 00:32:11,563
I'd like this please.

475
00:32:12,197 --> 00:32:13,198
Of course.

476
00:32:13,231 --> 00:32:15,567
- I saw the article in Miyavi.
- Thank you.

477
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:35,453
The skin lotion is selling hot.

478
00:32:36,054 --> 00:32:38,123
Miyavi's sales are growing too.

479
00:32:38,156 --> 00:32:39,858
All right!

480
00:32:39,891 --> 00:32:41,326
Your debut article is in it.

481
00:32:41,993 --> 00:32:44,029
Yup, a great 200-letters.

482
00:32:44,062 --> 00:32:45,463
Thank you.

483
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:03,682
Can you all gather around
for a second?

484
00:33:06,952 --> 00:33:08,119
It's been decided.

485
00:33:09,387 --> 00:33:10,789
Miyavi will be discontinued.

486
00:33:13,191 --> 00:33:14,759
You all did great.

487
00:33:16,862 --> 00:33:21,633
I'm really proud that I was able
to make this magazine with you.

488
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:29,941
I will never forget you.

489
00:33:44,055 --> 00:33:45,257
What do you want?

490
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:50,595
I have a request.

491
00:33:53,164 --> 00:33:57,535
I don't know where I'll be assigned
after the merger.

492
00:33:58,570 --> 00:34:01,606
But please let me be
your assistant again.

493
00:34:04,809 --> 00:34:06,378
You still want to do odd jobs?

494
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:12,918
I want to be a part of a team
that makes something together.

495
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:16,154
Under your guidance.

496
00:34:20,992 --> 00:34:21,826
I...

497
00:34:23,695 --> 00:34:28,833
I always thought being normal
and average beat everything else.

498
00:34:30,535 --> 00:34:32,370
But watching you...

499
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:36,341
I couldn't help but be amazed
at how awesome you are.

500
00:34:37,642 --> 00:34:38,510
So please.

501
00:34:40,512 --> 00:34:42,013
Remember what you said before?

502
00:34:43,481 --> 00:34:45,884
That fashion lets people dream?

503
00:34:51,556 --> 00:34:52,424
You're right.

504
00:34:53,458 --> 00:34:55,927
This job is about
letting people dream.

505
00:34:58,296 --> 00:35:00,966
So it's not me
that you should be admiring.

506
00:35:02,367 --> 00:35:03,635
It's this job.

507
00:35:28,493 --> 00:35:29,361
It's OK'd!

508
00:35:51,883 --> 00:35:55,286
You've created
such a wonderful magazine.

509
00:36:00,892 --> 00:36:03,762
Thank you.

510
00:36:23,415 --> 00:36:24,449
Here.

511
00:36:25,817 --> 00:36:27,052
Thank you.

512
00:36:31,556 --> 00:36:32,390
Nami.

513
00:36:43,601 --> 00:36:45,003
There. Let's go.

514
00:36:50,175 --> 00:36:52,844
Isn't this hard to walk?

515
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:54,579
Stick close, and we'll be fine.

516
00:36:55,313 --> 00:36:56,548
Give me your hand.

517
00:37:09,461 --> 00:37:10,728
A receipt?

518
00:37:14,365 --> 00:37:15,533
I'll go buy tickets.

519
00:37:16,968 --> 00:37:18,736
- Ouch!
- Oops.

520
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:29,347
Hey...

521
00:37:41,826 --> 00:37:43,561
Ten things I want to do
when I get a boyfriend

522
00:37:43,595 --> 00:37:45,096
Huh?

523
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:50,502
"Be called in a deep voice."

524
00:37:51,035 --> 00:37:52,804
"Ride double on a bicycle."

525
00:37:53,404 --> 00:37:56,307
"Phone calls right after saying bye."

526
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:00,712
Did you just get off work?

527
00:38:02,313 --> 00:38:03,414
Get on.

528
00:38:03,748 --> 00:38:06,518
- What is it?
- I wanted to hear your voice.

529
00:38:06,551 --> 00:38:08,953
This is Nami, my girlfriend.

530
00:38:09,554 --> 00:38:12,090
Called in a deep voice,
double ride a bicycle...

531
00:38:13,992 --> 00:38:17,595
He saw this, and that's why...?

532
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:26,271
This scarf, too.

533
00:38:29,841 --> 00:38:32,377
He said something about a photo booth.

534
00:38:34,345 --> 00:38:35,380
But jeez.

535
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:38,883
I wrote this way back in junior high.

536
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:41,252
Tie a scarf together,
button off of uniform, photo booth...

537
00:38:44,489 --> 00:38:45,390
Nami.

538
00:38:47,358 --> 00:38:48,626
Here you go.

539
00:38:49,227 --> 00:38:50,528
Thank you.

540
00:38:50,562 --> 00:38:51,663
And one more thing.

541
00:38:52,664 --> 00:38:53,498
Before I forget.

542
00:39:00,038 --> 00:39:01,372
Thank you.

543
00:39:04,442 --> 00:39:05,643
Junnosuke.

544
00:39:06,377 --> 00:39:07,779
I want to do a photo booth.

545
00:39:08,246 --> 00:39:10,114
I knew it!

546
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:12,383
I bet they have one.

547
00:39:13,051 --> 00:39:13,818
Let's go.

548
00:39:25,563 --> 00:39:29,367
This is a first.
You inviting me for lunch.

549
00:39:31,102 --> 00:39:32,003
Yes.

550
00:39:32,904 --> 00:39:34,405
And probably the last.

551
00:39:38,773 --> 00:39:44,045
So, have you come to butter up to me
now that the merger is official?

552
00:39:45,079 --> 00:39:50,618
Mr. Ugajin has already asked me
to make sure your editors are safe.

553
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:53,521
He did?

554
00:39:53,788 --> 00:39:54,622
Yes.

555
00:39:55,489 --> 00:40:00,428
He'd been gathering information
to protect you and your magazine.

556
00:40:01,362 --> 00:40:03,164
He even came to me.

557
00:40:04,765 --> 00:40:07,535
We had an executive meeting today.

558
00:40:07,835 --> 00:40:09,270
With this merger,

559
00:40:09,303 --> 00:40:14,208
all the magazines from Otowado
will be discontinued.

560
00:40:16,043 --> 00:40:16,977
Except...

561
00:40:18,746 --> 00:40:19,980
...for Miyavi.

562
00:40:24,285 --> 00:40:29,824
There's a throng of big brands now
wanting to collaborate with Miyavi.

563
00:40:29,857 --> 00:40:35,830
So our company has no choice
but to keep Miyavi in print.

564
00:40:36,864 --> 00:40:37,631
Right.

565
00:40:38,165 --> 00:40:39,500
Gather everyone up!

566
00:40:40,201 --> 00:40:41,569
Miyavi is back.

567
00:40:41,735 --> 00:40:43,437
It's going to survive!

568
00:40:47,007 --> 00:40:49,243
You all deserve it.

569
00:40:54,515 --> 00:40:55,516
Really?

570
00:40:56,317 --> 00:40:57,284
It's not going out?

571
00:40:57,751 --> 00:41:00,955
I'm so glad, thank you!

572
00:41:03,257 --> 00:41:04,525
Miyavi gets to continue!

573
00:41:04,558 --> 00:41:05,693
Good for you!

574
00:41:07,128 --> 00:41:08,129
Congratulations.

575
00:41:08,162 --> 00:41:09,396
If Miyavi stays in print,

576
00:41:09,430 --> 00:41:12,266
your position as
editor-in-chief is safe.

577
00:41:14,101 --> 00:41:16,237
What a perfect scenario.

578
00:41:17,438 --> 00:41:20,975
That was your intention
in the first place, wasn't it?

579
00:41:23,344 --> 00:41:24,411
But...

580
00:41:25,379 --> 00:41:27,114
There's one condition.

581
00:41:28,849 --> 00:41:31,051
For Miyavi to stay in print.

582
00:41:32,386 --> 00:41:37,591
Reiko Horai must step down
from editor-in-chief.

583
00:41:39,894 --> 00:41:44,598
That article wasn't factored in,
was it?

584
00:41:52,206 --> 00:41:53,274
Look.

585
00:41:54,975 --> 00:41:57,811
Do you know why I became
Miyavi's editor-in-chief?

586
00:41:59,747 --> 00:42:04,418
No matter how hard the situation,
fashion magazines must continue on.

587
00:42:07,221 --> 00:42:11,926
The excitement of the readers
as they pick up the latest copy.

588
00:42:12,893 --> 00:42:15,296
Hearts fluttering with each page.

589
00:42:16,030 --> 00:42:17,565
Discovering dreams through fashion.

590
00:42:18,165 --> 00:42:21,202
That's how we came
to work in this industry too.

591
00:42:23,204 --> 00:42:26,006
There is value in printed magazines.

592
00:42:28,042 --> 00:42:32,646
Miyavi was created with the passion
to bring Japan's mode to the world.

593
00:42:35,449 --> 00:42:40,154
Miyavi must continue
in order for this industry to survive.

594
00:42:41,989 --> 00:42:43,858
So I paved a path.

595
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,896
And now, I leave.

596
00:42:54,735 --> 00:42:56,136
From here on out,

597
00:42:57,371 --> 00:42:59,773
I leave it to
my editors and assistants.

598
00:43:03,644 --> 00:43:05,179
And to you.

599
00:43:08,882 --> 00:43:10,684
Why must she be fired?

600
00:43:10,918 --> 00:43:13,320
We're being taken over.

601
00:43:13,687 --> 00:43:16,156
We can't challenge their conditions.

602
00:43:17,091 --> 00:43:18,926
She's the best out there.

603
00:43:20,694 --> 00:43:22,396
I can't agree to it.

604
00:43:22,429 --> 00:43:25,900
But Ms. Horai has.

605
00:43:29,637 --> 00:43:31,872
Oh no, it's coming!

606
00:43:35,809 --> 00:43:37,044
I'm going to fall!

607
00:43:47,421 --> 00:43:49,423
Are you okay?

608
00:43:49,456 --> 00:43:50,691
I'm fine.

609
00:43:54,361 --> 00:43:56,263
An ice skating rink.

610
00:43:57,464 --> 00:43:58,932
I didn't know they had one.

611
00:44:03,637 --> 00:44:07,808
I haven't skated in a long time.
I kind of want to now.

612
00:44:09,943 --> 00:44:11,845
Hold hands and ice skate
Be gifted a single flower

613
00:44:12,413 --> 00:44:13,247
Okay.

614
00:44:14,148 --> 00:44:15,749
- Really?
- Really.

615
00:44:24,458 --> 00:44:26,360
There's hardly anybody else.

616
00:44:27,061 --> 00:44:28,295
I guess not.

617
00:44:33,701 --> 00:44:35,636
Reserved

618
00:44:41,809 --> 00:44:43,711
Are you okay, Nami?

619
00:44:43,744 --> 00:44:46,280
I've never skated before.

620
00:44:53,787 --> 00:44:54,688
Nami!

621
00:45:02,996 --> 00:45:05,566
Nami, you're so bad at this.

622
00:45:05,966 --> 00:45:08,669
I told you I've never skated before.

623
00:45:15,409 --> 00:45:17,311
Where did you get that?

624
00:45:32,359 --> 00:45:33,360
For you.

625
00:45:40,868 --> 00:45:41,902
Thank you.

626
00:45:44,471 --> 00:45:45,339
I...

627
00:45:46,940 --> 00:45:49,176
If it means I can watch you smile...

628
00:45:50,010 --> 00:45:54,681
I'll keep giving you flowers
until you're an old grandma.

629
00:45:57,551 --> 00:45:58,886
Junnosuke.

630
00:46:43,831 --> 00:46:44,731
Nami.

631
00:46:46,733 --> 00:46:48,302
Can I make a wish too?

632
00:46:49,970 --> 00:46:50,737
Yes.

633
00:46:53,340 --> 00:46:55,108
Will you be my wife?

634
00:46:58,312 --> 00:47:01,748
I'm quitting photography
to run my family's business.

635
00:47:04,918 --> 00:47:06,687
Come to Kanazawa with me.
